      <section id="rule-of-72">
        <h2>The Rule of 72: A Mental Shortcut</h2>
        <p>
          The Rule of 72 is a back-of-the-envelope trick to estimate how long it takes your money to <strong>double</strong> at a given annual return:
        </p>

        <div class="callout formula-callout">
          <p><strong>Years to double = 72 ÷ Annual interest rate (%)</strong></p>
        </div>

        <h3>Quick Examples</h3>
        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Annual Return</th>
