                <td>9 years</td>
                <td>FD / PPF / hybrid fund</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>10%</td>
                <td>7.2 years</td>
                <td>Balanced equity fund</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>12%</td>
                <td>6 years</td>
                <td>Equity mutual fund (long-term avg)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>15%</td>
                <td>4.8 years</td>
                <td>Aggressive equity (best case)</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>
          At 12% returns, ₹1 lakh becomes ₹2 lakh in 6 years, ₹4 lakh in 12 years, ₹8 lakh in 18 years, and ₹16 lakh in 24 years. This is why equity SIPs over 20-25 years can produce life-changing wealth.
          The same compounding idea applies in reverse when you borrow on a long fixed-rate loan: early payments are interest-heavy before principal drops—see how
          <a href="/calculator/mortgage/">mortgage interest compounds over 30 years</a> in a full year-by-year schedule.
        </p>
      </section>

